11:02.120 --> 11:03.913
a good news/bad news thing here.

11:03.955 --> 11:05.624
(sighs)

11:05.665 --> 11:08.209
Your mom lost her job,

11:05.665 --> 11:08.209
and we're pretty broke.

11:08.251 --> 11:11.087
The good news is, that makes

11:08.251 --> 11:11.087
your tuition an issue.

11:11.129 --> 11:14.715
Now, I think I can talk her

11:11.129 --> 11:14.715
into letting you come home.

11:14.757 --> 11:16.551
Dad, no, I can't come home!

11:16.593 --> 11:18.428
Marlin Academy

11:16.593 --> 11:18.428
is the best thing

11:18.470 --> 11:19.929
that has ever

11:18.470 --> 11:19.929
happened to me.

11:19.971 --> 11:21.764
I am at a crucial point

11:19.971 --> 11:21.764
in my rehabilitation.

11:21.806 --> 11:23.975
Uh-huh. What's her name?

11:24.017 --> 11:26.685
That's the thing--

11:24.017 --> 11:26.685
there's, like, ten of them!

11:27.562 --> 11:29.356
(knock at door)

11:29.397 --> 11:32.526
Check the peephole.

11:32.567 --> 11:35.028
If they've got a hand truck,

11:32.567 --> 11:35.028
don't open it.

11:35.069 --> 11:36.737
(knocking continues)

11:36.779 --> 11:38.781
(door opens, closes)

11:38.823 --> 11:40.575
Craig, what are

11:38.823 --> 11:40.575
you doing here?

11:40.617 --> 11:42.785
Lois, I just had a meeting

11:40.617 --> 11:42.785
with Mr. Pinter--

11:42.827 --> 11:44.787
well, more like an hour

11:42.827 --> 11:44.787
begging, really--

11:44.829 --> 11:47.207
but the point is, you can

11:44.829 --> 11:47.207
have your old job back!

11:47.248 --> 11:48.333
Yes!

11:48.375 --> 11:51.419
Craig, that is such good news!

11:51.461 --> 11:53.754
And all you have to do

11:51.461 --> 11:53.754
is apologize.

11:53.796 --> 11:57.133
And let him dock your pay

11:53.796 --> 11:57.133
150 bucks.

11:57.175 --> 11:59.135
And you have to work

11:57.175 --> 11:59.135
the graveyard shift

11:59.177 --> 12:00.637
for a couple months.

12:00.679 --> 12:01.762
Oh.

12:01.804 --> 12:03.557
Sounds good, Mom.

12:03.598 --> 12:04.765
No, thanks.

12:03.598 --> 12:04.765
What?!

12:04.807 --> 12:06.434
You're kidding!

12:04.807 --> 12:06.434
Why?!

12:06.476 --> 12:08.769
Because  that's like admitting

12:06.476 --> 12:08.769
he's right.

12:08.811 --> 12:10.271
I'm not going to do that.

12:10.313 --> 12:12.440
Lois, if this makes

12:10.313 --> 12:12.440
any difference,

12:12.482 --> 12:15.776
I will work every graveyard

12:12.482 --> 12:15.776
shift right alongside you--

12:15.818 --> 12:17.612
every single one of them.

12:17.654 --> 12:18.779
Oh, hi, Craig.

12:17.654 --> 12:18.779
What's going on?

12:18.821 --> 12:20.781
Nothing. Just business.

12:20.823 --> 12:23.410
Take it easy, tiger.

12:23.451 --> 12:24.994
We're working.

12:25.036 --> 12:26.538
Well, I am.

12:27.288 --> 12:28.707
Hi.

12:28.747 --> 12:30.749
Back to the grind.

12:32.085 --> 12:34.546
Nice guy.

12:43.054 --> 12:44.889
WOMAN:

12:43.054 --> 12:44.889
Thank you, Tanya.

12:44.931 --> 12:47.434
Tanya, that was

12:44.931 --> 12:47.434
fantastic.

12:47.475 --> 12:49.394
I swear, when you

12:47.475 --> 12:49.394
put tap to it,

12:49.436 --> 12:51.896
the Pledge of Allegiance

12:49.436 --> 12:51.896
just comes alive.

12:51.938 --> 12:54.857
One suggestion:

12:51.938 --> 12:54.857
do you have a tube top?

12:54.899 --> 12:57.277
Oh, Francis, you are

12:54.899 --> 12:57.277
just wonderful.

12:57.318 --> 13:00.447
I mean, you're so different

12:57.318 --> 13:00.447
than the local boys.

13:00.488 --> 13:03.074
I mean, I haven't even

13:00.488 --> 13:03.074
known you that long,

13:03.116 --> 13:06.202
and I already feel

13:03.116 --> 13:06.202
so connected to you.

13:06.244 --> 13:08.079
I know. It's almost mystical.

13:08.121 --> 13:11.999
Yeah. And I'm so glad the

13:08.121 --> 13:11.999
gay thing isn't an issue.

13:12.041 --> 13:13.834
You're gay?

13:13.876 --> 13:16.713
No, no, silly--  you  are.

13:16.755 --> 13:18.673
Wait, you think I'm gay?

13:18.715 --> 13:20.717
Oh, you don't have to

13:18.715 --> 13:20.717
hide anything, honey.

13:20.759 --> 13:22.469
I mean, we're a lot

13:20.759 --> 13:22.469
more liberal here

13:22.510 --> 13:23.844
than you think we are.

13:23.886 --> 13:26.847
I mean, it's not

13:23.886 --> 13:26.847
like Birmingham.

13:26.889 --> 13:29.850
Wait a minute--

13:26.889 --> 13:29.850
you think I'm gay?

13:29.892 --> 13:31.227
Why do you think I'm gay?

13:31.269 --> 13:32.853
Oh, come on.

13:32.895 --> 13:35.482
You like the theater,

13:32.895 --> 13:35.482
you're good with decorating,

13:35.523 --> 13:38.901
and, well, you're completely

13:35.523 --> 13:38.901
obsessed with your mother.

13:38.943 --> 13:41.112
Can you undo my hooks?

13:42.530 --> 13:45.032
Tanya, I'm kind of having

13:42.530 --> 13:45.032
a dilemma here...

13:45.074 --> 13:48.869
Oh, great.

13:45.074 --> 13:48.869
Frannie, can you spray me?

13:48.911 --> 13:50.121
My suit keeps riding up.

13:50.163 --> 13:51.372
(giggling)

13:54.125 --> 13:57.587
That's why I'm here...

13:54.125 --> 13:57.587
girlfriend.

14:03.802 --> 14:05.679
So what did you

14:03.802 --> 14:05.679
want to talk about?

14:05.720 --> 14:07.888
I'm your teacher.

14:05.720 --> 14:07.888
Can't we just talk?

14:07.930 --> 14:10.891
You know, that

14:07.930 --> 14:10.891
Julie Houlerman

14:10.933 --> 14:13.812
is a very special

14:10.933 --> 14:13.812
little girl.

14:13.852 --> 14:15.522
Oh, come on!

14:15.563 --> 14:16.731
Caroline,

14:15.563 --> 14:16.731
I don't want to...

14:16.773 --> 14:18.899
Malcolm, Malcolm, Malcolm.

14:18.941 --> 14:21.902
So private, so guarded.

14:21.944 --> 14:24.905
But you don't have to

14:21.944 --> 14:24.905
be that way with me.

14:24.947 --> 14:27.367
I'm on your side.

14:27.408 --> 14:30.495
Julie knows that-- she's

14:27.408 --> 14:30.495
not even in my class.

14:30.537 --> 14:32.539
She talked to you?

14:30.537 --> 14:32.539
About me?

14:32.580 --> 14:33.832
What'd she say?

14:33.873 --> 14:37.502
Aw, nothing that wasn't

14:33.873 --> 14:37.502
obvious already.

14:37.544 --> 14:39.003
You know, when you

14:37.544 --> 14:39.003
open up to people,

14:39.045 --> 14:41.172
you will always

14:39.045 --> 14:41.172
be surprised

14:41.214 --> 14:44.300
just how well

14:41.214 --> 14:44.300
things turn out.

14:44.342 --> 14:47.470
ALL:

14:44.342 --> 14:47.470
Surprise!

14:51.641 --> 14:53.017
Isn't it wonderful?

14:53.059 --> 14:54.935
Julie organized

14:54.977 --> 14:57.188
the whole thing herself,

14:54.977 --> 14:57.188
and everyone

14:57.230 --> 14:59.148
in school responded.

14:59.190 --> 15:02.109
Dear Malcolm, this

14:59.190 --> 15:02.109
isn't just food.

15:02.151 --> 15:04.945
It's an expression of how

15:02.151 --> 15:04.945
we all feel about you.

15:04.987 --> 15:08.616
Our hearts go out to you

15:04.987 --> 15:08.616
in your time of need.

15:08.658 --> 15:10.910
(applause)

15:25.717 --> 15:27.844
You're going

15:25.717 --> 15:27.844
to keep the food?

15:25.717 --> 15:27.844
Yes.

15:27.886 --> 15:30.221
I'm not going to throw away

15:27.886 --> 15:30.221
perfectly good pie filling

15:30.263 --> 15:31.972
and... lamb chutney.

15:32.014 --> 15:34.141
Don't you even care

15:32.014 --> 15:34.141
how humiliating this is?

15:34.183 --> 15:35.852
REESE:

15:34.183 --> 15:35.852
We've done can drives.

15:35.894 --> 15:37.061
This is just the

15:35.894 --> 15:37.061
crap people find

15:37.103 --> 15:38.605
when they clean

15:37.103 --> 15:38.605
out the garage.

15:38.646 --> 15:39.689
Okay, just stop it.

15:39.731 --> 15:41.900
I know how

15:39.731 --> 15:41.900
hard this is,

15:41.941 --> 15:43.693
but no one ever said

15:41.941 --> 15:43.693
life is fair.

15:43.735 --> 15:45.069
Sometimes decent,

15:43.735 --> 15:45.069
hard-working people

15:45.111 --> 15:46.613
get dumped on

15:45.111 --> 15:46.613
for no good reason,

15:46.654 --> 15:47.988
and they just have

15:46.654 --> 15:47.988
to wipe out their eyes

15:48.030 --> 15:48.989
and keep on walking.

15:49.031 --> 15:51.242
Something will

15:49.031 --> 15:51.242
turn up.

15:51.284 --> 15:53.787
We just have to hold on

15:51.284 --> 15:53.787
a little bit longer.

15:53.828 --> 15:56.664
And in the meantime, be

15:53.828 --> 15:56.664
thankful for small favors.

15:56.706 --> 15:59.626
Anyone want the last olive?

15:59.667 --> 16:01.210
Those aren't olives.

16:01.252 --> 16:02.962
Those are peaches.

16:05.047 --> 16:06.966
(siren wailing)

16:09.886 --> 16:12.096
Well, you got him here

16:09.886 --> 16:12.096
early, that's good.

16:12.138 --> 16:13.932
He'll be fine

16:12.138 --> 16:13.932
in a few days.

16:13.973 --> 16:16.517
Just like when this

16:13.973 --> 16:16.517
one ate the frog.

16:16.559 --> 16:18.269
I only ate half of it.

16:18.311 --> 16:20.814
I won't put

16:18.311 --> 16:20.814
the stomach pump on the bill.

16:20.855 --> 16:23.608
I mean, he did most

16:20.855 --> 16:23.608
of the work on the way over.

16:23.650 --> 16:24.901
Thanks, Don. Uh...

16:24.943 --> 16:27.027
listen, as far

16:24.943 --> 16:27.027
as the bill goes,

16:27.069 --> 16:30.030
what kind of neighborhood

16:27.069 --> 16:30.030
are we in?

16:30.072 --> 16:31.616
Well... the emergency room,

16:31.658 --> 16:33.701
couple days

16:31.658 --> 16:33.701
of observation--

16:33.743 --> 16:35.202
probably three or four.

16:35.244 --> 16:38.038
Three or four...

16:35.244 --> 16:38.038
hun...?

16:54.347 --> 16:55.682
Okay.

16:55.723 --> 16:57.057
You boys take

16:55.723 --> 16:57.057
care of your dad.

16:57.099 --> 16:58.142
I'm going to go see Mr. Pinter

16:58.184 --> 16:59.435
and beg for my job back.

16:59.477 --> 17:00.520
What? Mom, wait.

17:00.561 --> 17:02.062
You don't have

17:00.561 --> 17:02.062
to do that.

17:02.104 --> 17:03.648
Yes, I do. I don't want to,

17:03.690 --> 17:05.441
shouldn't have to,

17:03.690 --> 17:05.441
but guess what?

17:05.483 --> 17:06.901
I do.

17:06.943 --> 17:08.486
But I want you boys

17:06.943 --> 17:08.486
to understand something.

17:08.528 --> 17:11.322
I am not going back

17:08.528 --> 17:11.322
on anything I said before.

17:11.364 --> 17:13.157
She's completely

17:11.364 --> 17:13.157
going back on it,

17:13.199 --> 17:15.952
but I'm not going

17:13.199 --> 17:15.952
to kick her when she's down.

17:15.994 --> 17:17.871
You're totally

17:15.994 --> 17:17.871
going back on it.

17:17.912 --> 17:19.079
No, I am not.

17:19.121 --> 17:21.499
Everything I said before

17:19.121 --> 17:21.499
still goes.

17:21.541 --> 17:22.792
You know, sometimes

17:21.541 --> 17:22.792
bad things happen

17:22.834 --> 17:24.752
and you don't

17:22.834 --> 17:24.752
understand why,

17:24.794 --> 17:27.964
and you just have to trust that

17:24.794 --> 17:27.964
there's a good reason for it.

17:29.590 --> 17:31.676
Sure, it's easy

17:29.590 --> 17:31.676
to work in mysterious ways

17:31.718 --> 17:33.928
when you  have  a job.

17:36.347 --> 17:39.099
(long, gassy whine)

17:39.141 --> 17:41.019
(farts)

17:41.060 --> 17:43.103
(groans)

17:43.145 --> 17:47.358
The first one who laughs

17:43.145 --> 17:47.358
gets their ass kicked.

17:50.820 --> 17:52.112
(moans)

17:52.154 --> 17:55.115
You have

17:52.154 --> 17:55.115
incredible hands.

17:55.157 --> 17:59.161
Well, it's easy

17:55.157 --> 17:59.161
on such a beautiful back.

17:59.203 --> 18:02.331
Not to mention

17:59.203 --> 18:02.331
the most talented...

18:02.373 --> 18:05.125
sweet...

18:05.167 --> 18:06.419
sexy...

18:09.338 --> 18:10.506
What?

18:10.548 --> 18:12.132
Francis...

18:12.174 --> 18:16.387
are... are you sure

18:12.174 --> 18:16.387
you're really...

18:16.429 --> 18:18.973
how you are?

18:20.182 --> 18:23.143
Tanya, I'm so confused.

18:23.185 --> 18:27.189
I mean, I thought that I was,

18:23.185 --> 18:27.189
but when I'm around you,

18:27.231 --> 18:30.985
I have these...

18:27.231 --> 18:30.985
strange, new feelings.

18:31.027 --> 18:36.699
I feel like...

18:31.027 --> 18:36.699
maybe I could... change.

18:38.200 --> 18:40.787
That you could be

18:38.200 --> 18:40.787
the woman who changes me.

18:40.828 --> 18:44.082
Oh, Francis...

18:44.123 --> 18:46.417
I was hoping you'd say that.

18:46.459 --> 18:48.377
I want to be that woman

18:48.419 --> 18:49.670
for you.

18:49.712 --> 18:51.672
Oh, and don't

18:49.712 --> 18:51.672
you worry, honey.

18:51.714 --> 18:54.634
If there's one thing

18:51.714 --> 18:54.634
we know how to do

18:54.675 --> 18:56.094
down here,

18:56.135 --> 18:58.805
it's how to fix this.

19:00.222 --> 19:02.058
MAN:

19:00.222 --> 19:02.058
And with God's help,

19:02.100 --> 19:04.894
we can say "no!" to weakness.

19:04.936 --> 19:08.564
We can say "no!"

19:04.936 --> 19:08.564
to all things unnatural!

19:08.606 --> 19:12.192
It is procreation,

19:08.606 --> 19:12.192
not recreation!

19:12.234 --> 19:16.196
And when Satan tempts us,

19:12.234 --> 19:16.196
what do we do?

19:16.238 --> 19:17.782
Pray out the gay.

19:17.824 --> 19:18.866
Get to it!

19:26.248 --> 19:28.375
I have to say, Lois,

19:26.248 --> 19:28.375
I'm surprised

19:28.417 --> 19:30.586
by this change

19:28.417 --> 19:30.586
in your attitude.

19:30.628 --> 19:32.379
Yeah, well, me, too.

19:32.421 --> 19:34.674
I know we've had

19:32.421 --> 19:34.674
our differences,

19:34.715 --> 19:37.259
but I hope that we

19:34.715 --> 19:37.259
can make all this

19:37.301 --> 19:39.095
water under the bridge.

19:39.137 --> 19:41.221
So, if you'll

19:39.137 --> 19:41.221
just sign here...

19:41.263 --> 19:42.473
Mm, what's this?

19:42.515 --> 19:44.058
Your apology.

19:44.100 --> 19:46.936
I think I captured

19:44.100 --> 19:46.936
your voice rather nicely.

19:46.978 --> 19:49.022
You want it in writing?

19:49.063 --> 19:50.272
Yes.

19:50.314 --> 19:52.232
Look, Lois, you can

19:50.314 --> 19:52.232
tell these clowns

19:52.274 --> 19:54.861
whatever you want--

19:52.274 --> 19:54.861
that I got on my knees

19:54.902 --> 19:57.113
and begged you to come

19:54.902 --> 19:57.113
back, I don't care.

19:57.155 --> 20:01.200
I just want you and I to

19:57.155 --> 20:01.200
know how things  really  are.

20:17.133 --> 20:18.300
That's not a signature.

20:18.342 --> 20:20.260
No, it's more

20:18.342 --> 20:20.260
of a suggestion.

20:20.302 --> 20:22.262
"The horse you rode in on"

20:20.302 --> 20:22.262
is optional.

20:22.304 --> 20:23.556
Now, look...

20:23.597 --> 20:24.724
No, you look.

20:24.765 --> 20:25.725
I don't deserve this.

20:25.766 --> 20:27.267
The only thing

20:25.766 --> 20:27.267
I ever did wrong

20:27.309 --> 20:29.269
was all the work I did

20:27.309 --> 20:29.269
to cover your butt.

20:29.311 --> 20:30.521
Well, we obviously

20:29.311 --> 20:30.521
have different

20:30.563 --> 20:31.772
definitions of "wrong."

20:31.814 --> 20:33.273
Yeah, I guess we do.

20:33.315 --> 20:34.942
For instance,

20:33.315 --> 20:34.942
I think it's wrong

20:34.984 --> 20:36.527
for you to put your name

20:34.984 --> 20:36.527
on sales reports

20:36.569 --> 20:38.278
that you didn't write.

20:38.320 --> 20:40.322
I think it's wrong you keep

20:38.320 --> 20:40.322
a little bag of "herbs"

20:40.364 --> 20:41.908
in your bottom left drawer.

20:41.949 --> 20:43.117
I think it's wrong

20:41.949 --> 20:43.117
you slept with

20:43.159 --> 20:44.160
the district manager's wife.

20:44.202 --> 20:45.912
And you want

20:44.202 --> 20:45.912
to know something?

20:45.953 --> 20:47.872
You don't even

20:45.953 --> 20:47.872
have to worry about it,

20:47.914 --> 20:51.458
because I also think it's wrong

20:47.914 --> 20:51.458
to blab this kind of thing.

20:51.500 --> 20:55.295
You know, you should be so glad

20:51.500 --> 20:55.295
that I'm the only one that knows

20:55.337 --> 20:57.673
this stuff about you.

20:57.715 --> 21:01.385
Anyone else here would sell you

20:57.715 --> 21:01.385
down the river in a second.

21:02.344 --> 21:04.304
(chuckles)

21:04.346 --> 21:07.307
God, I am so much

21:04.346 --> 21:07.307
better than you.

21:12.146 --> 21:13.355
(clears throat)

21:20.362 --> 21:23.323
Yeah, he just ran off

21:20.362 --> 21:23.323
and quit for no reason.

21:23.365 --> 21:25.367
Huh, who knows why?

21:25.409 --> 21:27.828
See, you do

21:25.409 --> 21:27.828
the right thing,

21:27.870 --> 21:31.290
and everything

21:27.870 --> 21:31.290
works out for the best.

21:32.625 --> 21:34.334
Clean.

21:34.376 --> 21:38.005
I have Ho Hos-- real Ho Hos.

21:38.047 --> 21:39.757
You know,

21:38.047 --> 21:39.757
I'm sure I'm neglecting

21:39.799 --> 21:42.551
my spiritual side, but...

21:39.799 --> 21:42.551
money rules.

21:42.593 --> 21:44.344
The best part is

21:44.386 --> 21:47.807
I can finally get everything

21:44.386 --> 21:47.807
straightened out with Julie.

21:47.848 --> 21:49.142
Hi, Malcolm.

21:49.183 --> 21:50.601
Look, we're not poor anymore!

21:50.643 --> 21:53.312
So I don't want any more

21:50.643 --> 21:53.312
of your stupid pity, okay?!

21:55.856 --> 21:58.067
That helped, right?
